column7: Upon completion of a B.S. Degree in Business Management and Marketing from Arizona State University Alan embarked upon a successful sales career as the regional representative for Levi Strauss and Citizen Watch Companies. Alan found a passion for real estate in 1984 when he began working for builders as an onsite agent. He became the exclusive representative for builders such as SBC Custom Homes, Jesse Hill Custom Homes, Standing Rock Custom Homes and LaBlonde Custom Homes. Working for Coldwell Banker in 2004 Alan was awarded the Top Producer with an excess of $30,000,000 in volume that year. In 2005 Alan once again had the opportunity to advance his career and improve client outcomes by becoming the managing partner of Distinctive Luxury Properties. Not only did he manage a small boutique real estate company, but he continued to develop ongoing relationships with builders, investors, home buyers and sellers. Distinctive Luxury Properties was acquired by Russ Lyon Sotheby’s International Realty in 2008. Alan is currently certified in short sales and foreclosures and is a Real Estate Special Commissioner for Maricopa County Superior Courts. After 32 years of experience have given Alan the professional edge to bring buyers and sellers together for successful transactions. A solid commitment to both clients and builders has given Alan the highest honor, referrals. Over 75% of new business comes from satisfied customers! When Alan isn’t fulfilling the dreams of the perfect home for a client he can be found enjoying snow and water skiing, scuba diving or competitive shooting with his son. Alan’s oldest son is the Chief Technical Officer for Russ Lyon Sotheby’s International Realty developing new, cutting edge web and marketing based technology for the company. Contact Alan at 602-692-7200 or alan.zieder@russlyon.com. Follow him on Facebook: Scottsdale Real Estate and Leisure http://www.facebook.com/pages/Scottsdale-Real-Estate-and-Leisure/310926172266234. Everything Creative Designs stages vacant homes as well as occupied homes. Our furnishings are trendy, sophisticated and always create the right look for our client’s target market. column7: Cathy Gilchrist-Colmar is a licensed agent and Realtor with over 30 years of experience in all phases of real estate. With a background in construction, appraisal services and mortgage and title operations, she understands not only the market, but is also sensitive to the processes and issues involved with every aspect of selling and purchasing property. This varied and layered history gives her a comprehensive understanding of the many different facets and intricacies of real estate transactions, as well as a passion for the business. A love of riding horses brought Cathy to the Rancho Santa Fe area over 20 years ago. After becoming completely enamored with the area, she combined her love of horses and real estate. Her broad base of knowledge gives her a valuable edge in providing clients with top-level advice. A Certified Negotiation Expert, Cathy is skilled at navigating complex negotiations and guiding her clients confidently and professionally through the process of purchasing and/or selling their homes. This has led to long-term personal relationships with them as well as numerous accolades throughout the industry. Cathy has been individually ranked among the top agents nationwide with her former company, and was presented with the “Chairman’s Circle Diamond Award” in back-to-back years. Her transactions include sales ranging from $238,000 to $28 million. In the last ten years, she and her business partner Clinton Selfridge have sold over $186 million, and they are currently representing over $66 million of property. However, when asked what sets her apart from others in her profession, Cathy says, “Developing and maintaining great relationships with my clients has always come first. My clients have seen my perseverance and tenacity in working toward their best interests - whether it’s in regards to negotiating, aggressive marketing, or in implementing creative solutions. They trust that I will work hard on their behalf.”

column7: Redefining the real estate experience ...The real estate profession is highly personal for me, and I pride myself on doing whatever it takes to ensure my clients’ goals are met. Born in Glendale, I’ve always loved Southern California, which has made it easy to fully submerge myself into the local real estate market. You could say I live and breathe it 365 days a year. Over the past 14 years, attention to detail has been at the core of my business model. Whether a buyer is looking to purchase their first home or their forever home, I understand that everything is on the line. By walking my clients through the necessary steps in a meticulous fashion, I prevent unwelcome surprises and ensure the smoothest home-buying experience. The market in SoCal is very competitive, yet I have the tools to help clients find their dream home in spite of that.An agent with strong technological and marketing skills is advantageous for anyone looking to sell their home or investment property. There is much more that can be done beyond simply taking a picture and listing the home on the MLS (multiple listing service). I will create a customized marketing plan that involves professional photos, laser drawn floor plans, drone videos, individual property websites, social media targeted ads, and more.I currently call Pasadena my home and I'm always buzzing around Los Angeles doing what I do best—selling real estate. You, too, can experience what it’s like to feel, as my client Angela Tucker put it, 'like I was (Chris’s) only client, at all times.' My license hangs at Pacific Union of the John Aaroe Group, where our focus is to be the 'ultimate California company.' You can count on me to be a consummate professional with a passion for everything I do; after all, being your Realtor is not something I take lightly. I'd love to chat and welcome you to contact me anytime.CalBRE #01475481

San Diego Design Consultant for Stoneside Blinds and Shades
 Allied Member, ASID and CID Certified Interior Designer #6533

 Stoneside's In-home and In-office services

 Selecting and ordering custom blinds and shades involves a lot of decisions - including selecting the right shades and materials, deciding on the best options and getting precise measurements for your windows. Relax... Our in-home design consultants make it easy. When you request a free in-home consultation, a designer will give you a call to schedule an appointment. They'll also ask you a few questions during the call to learn more about your needs and make the best use of that appointment time.

 During your in-home appointment, our designer will show you sample materials and shades so you can visualize what your new window coverings will look like in your space. They will walk you through all of your options and help you choose the ones that best meet your needs. Next, they will configure your order and give you an estimate for your review.

 When you are ready to move forward, the consultant will schedule an installer to come to your home or office to get the exact measurements of your windows so we can insure a perfect fit. The designer will then use these exact measurements to configure your shades in your shopping cart. Now you're all set to buy!

 When we've finished manufacturing your blinds to your exact specifications, our installer will call you to schedule the installation. He will install the shades at your convenience, show you how to operate your shades and make sure that everything is perfect before he leaves. If, for any reason, something's not right, he'll work with us to correct the matter so you don't have to.

 By utilizing our in-home design, measure and install services, we guarantee your happiness with a money back guarantee.

column7: As a Broker Associate and Luxury Real Estate Specialist with Pacific Sotheby's International Realty, I have been selling residential real estate throughout San Diego County, focusing primarily on the Central and Coastal Communities since 2000. I make it my goal to put my clients needs first and do the best possible job for each and every one. As a Certified Residential Specialist since 2006, I have earned and maintain this professional designation which shows my commitment to my profession through reaching very high standards of production as well as professional education. Currently, this designation is only awarded to approximately 28,000 Realtors across the United States. Additionally, I am a SFR (Short Sale and Foreclosure Resouce). This designation was awarded through the National Association of Realtors and CRS education, demonstrating my knowledge and committment to working with buyers and sellers of foreclosures and short sales. Another important part of my business is being a relocation specialist. I am uniquely qualified to help those moving both to and from San Diego County. I pride myself in listening to the clients needs and in helping them both sell or buy their home just about anywhere in the County. I am committed to providing the best in service to all of my clients and as a testimony to that end, approximately 85%+ of my business came from referrals consistently over the last several years. Being named a Five Star Real Estate Agent for the last two years is an honor and an acknowledgment of a level of excellence achieved by fewer than 7 percent of the real estate agents in San Diego. I also enjoy educating the buyer who comes to me through relocation or one of my fellow CRS designees. Sharing information and knowledge about the various communities that make up San Diego helps my clients who are relocating find the right place to call home. Working with all of my clients, including referrals, is always an honor and a pleasure. Specialties: Residential Real Estate Sales, Relocation, Income Property Sales, Buyer Representation, Tax-Deferred or 1031 Exchanges, Luxury Home Sales, Coastal Properties and more.

column7: Jason is excited to be continuing his Real Estate journey working closely with Bosa Development out of Vancouver and the new Savina project at the corner of Kettner & Ash in downtown San Diego. Jason and the Savina Team team are looking forward to the release of this property in the coming months. Prior to rejoining S&P Real Estate, Jason was working with Macdonald Development Corporation as the Director of Sales & Marketing for Lakestone. During his time in BC, Jason was a Property Specialist at Predator Ridge for Wesbild Holdings. Jason was an active part of the real estate community in Kelowna and is a licensed Realtor at LRE Lakestone Real Estate Ltd and a member of the Canadian Home Builders Association and UDI. Prior to returning to Canada in 2010, Jason was the Broker/Owner of Nexus 30 Properties in Las Vegas. The Las Vegas real estate market was going through a very dynamic and diverse time. Nexus 30 handled everything from Billion dollar listings on the Las Vegas strip to bank owned foreclosures. Jason was also the Director of Sales with Playground Destination Properties, an Intrawest Company from 2002 - 2006 and during his tenure oversaw projects in Lake Tahoe, CA and as Managing Broker at Lake Las Vegas, NV. Jason started his real estate career in 1995 with Milborne Real Estate in Vancouver and during that time led a wide variety of projects in several market segments. Specialties: Jason's real estate experience includes the real estate sales and marketing of resort, urban, condo-hotel, single family homes, village, high rise, mid rise, golf communities, and fractional real estate.

column7: Jon represents commercial tenants and buyers with lease renegotiations, renewals, relocations, expansions, forensic lease audits and building purchases.Under Jon's direction R.E.D. Strategies, Jon directed the Commercial Tenant effort at a large regional firm in San Diego where he was recognized as  one of  top commercial real estate brokers in San Diego from 2008 to 2010. This experience on the landlord side of the table gives Jon a distinct edge when implementing negotiating strategies for tenants. My name is Justin Tye and I am the designated broker for Active Realty, Inc. My team is ranked in the top 1% of all agents in Southern California's the Inland Valley with over 30 million dollars in sales 2013. I was born and raised in Southern, California. My wife and I have lived in Corona for 6 years and have a great appreciation for all that Southern California has to offer it's residents. Having relocated our family in the past, we have a great appreciation for what it's like to move into a new home in an unfamiliar area. Having a Beach Home is a wish for so many and I feel lucky to be an integral part of fulfilling that dream. A mother of 3 young boys and avid surfer, I spend much of my time in the ocean or on the sand. My business philosophy is a marriage of high expectations, hard work, and loyalty. My personal philosophy is balance and mindfulness. Integrity is non-negotiable. A little background about me.... I grew up in Northern California in a family of seven. My father is a native San Diegan, and both he my grandparents have been in the real estate business for over 50 years. It was a natural decision to follow in their footsteps in the real estate field. I find that I am naturally enthusiastic about where I live and work. San Diego is one of the finest places in the world and I am blessed to be a part of this community and to have had success in this rewarding industry. I am a graduate from the University of California at Santa Barbara, and earned a BA in Communications and Minor in Global Economics. While attending school, I received title as an All-American Waterpolo player. I was also a member of the United States Women’s National Water polo team, which won the Pan American games in 1996, in Cuba.

column7: With over 30 years of experience, Karen has worked throughout the highs and lows of the economic cycles of real estate markets. She represents buyers and sellers in many different areas of the San Diego region. Her familiarity with the diverse neighborhoods coupled with her enthusiasm and “can do” attitude is an invaluable asset to her loyal clientele. There’s nothing Karen loves more than negotiating on her seller’s behalf helping them obtain top dollar for their home. It’s because of her robust knowledge, experience and expertise that she is able to accomplish this time and time again. When working with buyers, her greatest pleasure is finding their dream home and seeing the joy it brings them. Karen centers her business on providing outstanding customer service and is often overheard saying ”It’s my pleasure to serve you.” Her energy is contagious and work ethic unrivaled. Karen is proud to be affiliated with Pacific Sotheby's International Realty, named the Best Real Estate Brokerage by the San Diego Union-Tribune and one of the fastest growing private companies in San Diego County. When your hom is listed with Karen, you have the power of Pacific Sotheby's Realty's 17 offices in San Diego behind you, as well as a global real estate network encompassing over 750 offices in over 60 countries and territories. Her involvement with the community and the San Diego Board of Realtors ensures that she is in constant touch with the future of a rapidly changing region. Karen also believes that it is important to give back to the community. For the past six years Karen has made a donation on behalf of every closed sale to the Charitable Foundation, which donates to many different San Diego organizations, and The Sunshine Kids, which helps children with cancer. column7: Kevin Brown, Senior Global Real Estate Advisor and Associate Broker for Sotheby's International Realty, is recognized as one of Manhattan's most respected real estate professionals. A former owner and chairman of Century 21 NY Metro and, prior to that, a partner of Ashforth Warburg Real Estate (now Warburg Realty), Kevin is one of the city's premier luxury townhouse, co-op and condominium brokers. With over 20 years of sales experience, Kevin has successfully represented heads of state, CEOs of major companies, as well as countless referrals from friends and colleagues. Kevin began his professional career studying for a life in the priesthood with the Maryknoll Fathers. Kevin's interest in the work of the Maryknoll missionaries has only grown stronger over time. Maryknoll missionaries (www.maryknoll.org), since 1911, have consistently tried to help people overseas build communities of faith. Today, some work in war zones with refugees, and others minister to the sick, the elderly, orphans or people with AIDS. Another organization that Kevin is very proud to support is Action Against Hunger (www.actionagainsthunger.org). Recognized worldwide as a leader in the fight against hunger, Action Against Hunger delivers programs in over 40 countries, specializing in emergency situations of war, conflict and natural disasters and longer-term assistance to people in distress. Their ultimate goal is to help vulnerable populations regain their self-sufficiency for long-term sustainability. With a master's degree in Theology from Fordham University as well as an MBA in Finance from Baruch College, Kevin combines his passion for real estate with his lifelong commitment to numerous charitable organizations. To that end, a portion of the commissions he receives is frequently directed back to his client's favorite charity.

I have unique insight and empathy for the day to day challenges an escrow officer encounters and can use that common bond in my leadership role to help them realize their wants, needs & goals at the branch level. I am a wife and mother of two that is simply happy with life. I have been selling real estate for 8 years after coming from auto lending industry for 8 years. Real Estate has always been my passion! In my early twenties, (yes, I’m not in my twenties anymore), I used to drive down the streets looking for open house signs. I would get so excited to walk into a home and see what the floor plan and décor looked like. I would picture myself getting the keys to that house and walking inside with a pride ready to make it a HOME. I am guessing it came from a life of growing up in apartment complexes. This experience is what I want for all my clients; that same feeling of happiness and joy of buying their first or move-up home. Whatever that process takes, I am willing to take it on with them. I come from a career of customer service, and believe that it should be given at all times. My definition of customer service is 'Identifying a client’s needs and providing them with a service they expect and enjoy, by informing them with honest facts, giving my opinion when asked, and delivering their expectations in a timely manner'. I grew up a Midwesterner. Good ol' midwestern values. Family first, being polite, saying hello to random people on the street, opening doors for my wife, those types of things. I also grew up in a real estate family. My mom(real estate agent) and her partner have been buying, remodeling and selling homes since I can remember. My weekends often included various jobs around the current project. Landscaping, painting, the easy stuff a kid could do. I graduated from Purdue University(Boiler up!) on December 23rd 2003 and was working in California by December 29th. I got out of dodge as quickly as possible. Peace out Indiana. My good friend got me hitched up with a national home builder. At the time(2003) this home builder was churning out 4 homes a day. Seriously, 4 homes each day. I started on the customer service/construction side, moved into new home sales shortly thereafter and started selling high rises in downtown San Diego. After selling out those condos I transitioned into traditional resale and never looked back. Over the last 9 years I've immersed myself in many different facets of the real estate industry that has given me a very well rounded knowledge base.  This experience has landed me in different roles including Managing Director(Canter Brokerage), Team Leader/Mentor (The Middleton Group) and now Sales Manager with Renovation Realty.  I work with all kinds of clients from low end renovation seekers to high dollar international buyers.  What you get with me is an honest, hard working, and very experienced agent. I'm an expert negotiator, can be bull nosed when needed and heavy hearted just the same. I'm an expert marketer using a mix of traditional and new age methods. I'm a non-certified non-licensed therapist, so if you're a little bit crazy, I can dig it. We're all a little crazy, that's what makes it fun! So now that I've rambled on and eventually called you crazy, give me a call! Seriously though, call me. Let me know how I can help.

column7: We started out with the purchase of our first home in 1999. We then partnered & purchased a 7 unit apartment complex near SDSU which needed a makeover and I discovered how much I love turning the "ugly" duckling into something "pretty." We managed that complex for 11 years until we sold it. We both got our real estate licenses in order to invest in property (Kevin 1st, then myself, 2002 & 2003). We worked as Resident Managers at Time for Living Property Management for 2 years in Hillcrest on 6th Avenue (now a condo conversion). At the time, we managed those 18 units along with our 7 units plus our home for income as well as helping others buy and sell. Our first home value doubled in price and so we sold it. Things in San Diego we're maxed out, so we decided to purchase out of state as well where prices were much less. Would not recommend that, but got plenty of "hard-knocks" experience. San Diego is the best! The first brokerage we joined was Prudential California Realty in La Jolla and got Rookie of the Year our 1st year in real estate. Our average was about 2 home sales per month our 1st year. We purchased a town home in UTC, owner carry. We lived in UTC for about 2 years before we decided to start a family and wanted to settle down into a home with a large backyard near Kevin's parents with a view of Mt. Helix. When moving to east county we joined Remax and then Kevin got his broker's license & opened Conover Realty Inc. We enjoy meeting new people, helping them buy and sell, having fun with our kids in the Sunny San Diego weather. Kevin is from Ocean Beach and I'm from Clairemont. All our family is here and we love it! If you are relocating here and have any questions about San Diego, call me! We build our business on referrals by friends, family, current and past clients. We'll take good care of whomever you pass along & reward you very well!

As a 4th generation San Diegan, I chose the real estate profession as a result of my love for the city. Despite experiencing what some call the Global Recession, nearly a decade later my passion for the industry is unwavering. I considers myself a purveyor of the American Dream. I believe with a little planning and a lot of perseverance home ownership is not only attainable but still the right of every American. In 2006, I was proud to participate in the renaissance of Downtown San Diego. Working with urban in-fill developers, I have sold nearly 300 units in East Village, Cortez Hill, Little Italy and Mission Hills. In-depth market research, project positioning, strategic buyer qualification, product development, and design coordination are part of an unparalleled skill set I acquired while working in new construction. I was the first recipient of the Building Industry of America’s Greatest Award for Urban Leadership, an honor for which I was nominated by my peers. Described by my clients as “a high-energy professional with remarkable attention to detail and a drive for results”, I pride myself on communication and accessibility. I am focused on delivering quality of service, integrity and trust. I recognize buying or selling a home is an intimate milestone and I remain committed to crafting a personalized experience for each client.

column7: Are you looking for someone that will listen, advise, and guide you through the entire buying or selling process? Meet Martha, the very passionate, friendly and professional REALTOR®, architectural designer/consultant! A graduate of University of Southern California (USC) with a bachelor degree in Architecture, Martha had practiced architecture for more than 10 years in Los Angeles, where she called home for 20 years. Trained as an architect and REALTOR®, Martha is creative, solid and unique. Because she can put architecture and real estate together, she can help you sell by sharing that vision with buyers and agents. Because of her design background, she can help you find your dream home by helping you envision, define and organize the spaces in the homes. Working hard is her trademark. In contrast to many realtors, Martha is extremely patient, meticulous, focused and responsive. She is here to help you get to the next stage in life, whether you want to buy or sell. She walks you through each and every decision while she guides you in every step of the way. She explains everything, so you are comfortable with the entire process. She follows up on every detail, so your transaction is smooth and painless. Because she has your best interest at heart, you know you can count on her. Everything is in control, when you have Martha represent you. Dedicated to providing you quality service, Martha is here to help you realize your real estate goals and dreams! Martha and her husband love to travel, enjoy music, and are both fond of arts, history, and architecture. Martha loves snowboarding in winter, and swimming or ice-skating in summer. Aside from English, Martha speaks Chinese and Taiwanese, as well. She can also read and write Chinese.

column7: I've been a realtor for twelve years, specializing in the downtown high-rise market with my team, Scott-Finn & Associates. We are proudly a part of Pacific Sotheby's International - the top selling luxury brokerage in 92101. My team and I are top producers; we know our business, we aim to earn lifetime clients, and we are highly caffeinated. We did over $40 million in sales in 2016, earning rave reviews from our clients. We are 7 realtors and 2 full-time staff members, we are working for our clients 365 days a year.Located Downtown, Scott-Finn & Associates offers 92101 expertise. We know every building, current market values, and important public project plans in each neighborhood. We specialize downtown, but we sell homes from Imperial Beach to Oceanside. We all come with varied backgrounds and specializations; very likely, we do work your neighborhood.Backed by the Sotheby’s International brand, we position every home we list – from the studio to the penthouse – in the best possible light. There is no brokerage that can offer our marketing exposure, and our team leverages that opportunity to the fullest.I have extensive experience with historical homes near Balboa Park and on the coast. I have had great success for clients with my information-packed negotiating, diplomacy skills during escrow, and detailed management of the transaction details.I come equipped with a Political Science degree from UCLA, an entrepreneurial spirit, and a lot of energy. I volunteer with Voices for Children and I always vote. I’m a fine food, live music & wine lover with improving culinary skills, but a fish taco and a cold beer always hits home with a San Diego native like me.

Currently, I am a founding partner of Hoffman & Forde, Attorneys at Law, in San Diego, California.I received my Bachelor of Arts in Political Science and Spanish from the Davidson College in spring of 2002. While attending Davidson, I served as president of the NC Theta Chapter of Sigma Alpha Epsilon, chairman of the Inter-Fraternity Council and captain of the rugby team. I also played football at Davidson and was named to the Southern Conference Academic Honor Roll. After graduation, I moved to Washington, D.C. where I clerked for Congressman Duncan Hunter, Chairman of the House Armed Services Committee. While in Washington, I served as liaison between the Congressman’s Office and the Pentagon.I earned my Juris Doctor from California Western School of Law in spring of 2007. During law school, I was named to the Dean’s List and interned for the securities law firm of Robbins Umeda & Fink. Upon graduation, I joined Epsten Grinnell & Howell, a prominent real estate firm, focusing on homeowner association and construction defect law.  I then took on the job of establishing the Loan Modification Department for the formerly largest largest consumer law firm in San Diego. I have reviewed over 2,000 loan modification applications and have conducted numerous seminars educating attorneys on developing areas Loan Modification Law throughout California and Arizona.I am fluent in Spanish.  I am also a Sergeant in the San Diego County Honorary Deputy Sheriff's Assocation. I am an avid surfer and native San Diegan who remains active in the local community, having volunteered over 500 hours to Protection & Advocacy, Inc., a non-profit, disability rights advocacy firm. I am licensed to practice law in the state of California and a member of the State Bar of California and the San Diego County Bar Association.

Tess Chaney, CRP joined Martha Turner Sotheby’s International Realty in 2014 as Relocation Director. She drives sales within the company developing business with corporate relocation and referrals. Highly-mindful of the importance of participation and visibility, Tess regularly attends networking conferences. Tess also participates in several local charity events. Her welcoming personality builds strong relationships throughout the industry. Tess is a contributing writer for MOBILITY Magazine, a distinguished speaker at relocation conferences, and an industry expert for radio talk show, “Real Estate Matters with Stewart Title.” She is constantly streamlining and improving the relocation process. Tess utilizes the latest technology to improve her team’s efficiency in assisting transferees. Tess invests in her continuing professional education by attending workforce mobility conferences. Here she has the opportunity to benchmark her programs with the expertise of leading professionals in the industry. An eighth generation Texan, native Houstonian and graduate of Texas Christian University in Fort Worth, Tess began her real estate career in 2008 as a sales associate. After transitioning to a luxury firm she continued her success through closing multi-million dollar transactions and earned her Texas Broker’s License in 2010. In 2011, Tess began working in relocation. In 2012, she was promoted to Relocation Director. Tess has earned relocation’s highest certification, Certified Relocation Professional (CRP) demonstrating her long-term commitment to the global workforce mobility industry.
